{
  "text": "Prior work published on this subject includes [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . This paper will focus on the power requirements of the early development stages of the lunar base. The paper assumes a lunar base sited at the South Pole near the Shackleton crater and that power generation will be based on an initial photovoltaic and regenerative fuel cell (PV/RFC) power source. Figure 1 illustrates a notional Phase 0 base layout. High-level trade studies for energy storage and power management and distribution (PMAD) systems are presented and potential technology gaps/risks are identified.",
  "correct_citation": {
